Always use the GOV.UK colour palette.

## Colour contrast
The colour contrast ratio for text and interactive elements should be at least 4.5:1 as recommended by the W3C. Test your service to meet this standard.

## Sass variables
Use the Sass variables listed below, so you'll get any updates to the GOV.UK palette when you update GOV.UK Frontend.


## Main colours

{% for groupName, group in colours.main %}

  ### {{groupName}}

  <table class="govuk-body app-c-colour-list">

    {% for colour in group %}

      <tr class="app-c-colour-list-row">

        <td class="app-c-colour-list-column app-c-colour-list-column--swatch">
          <span class="app-c-swatch" style="background-color:{{colour.colour}}"></span>
        </td>
        <td class="app-c-colour-list-column app-c-colour-list-column--name">
          {{colour.name}}
        </td>
        <td class="app-c-colour-list-column app-c-colour-list-column--colour">
          {{colour.colour}}
        </td>
        <td class="app-c-colour-list-column app-c-colour-list-column--notes">
          {{colour.notes}}
        </td>

      </tr>

    {% endfor %}

  </table>

{% endfor %}

## Extended colours

